[3] Reports from various countries:

Asia - India (Delhi). 23 Jul 2011. Dengue fever has returned to the
city as the Municipal Corporation of Delhi today [23 Jul 2011]
reported one death due to the infection and 6 new cases in the past
one month, taking the total count of people affected by the virus this
year to 11. Last year [2010], a total of 6229 dengue cases had been
reported from the city, out of which 8 patients had died
http://news.outlookindia.com/item.aspx?728676. [A
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Delhi can be accessed at
http://healthmap.org/r/01Jf. - Mod.TY]

Indian Ocean - Maldives. 24 Jul 2011. A 22-year-old man being treated
for dengue fever at the Indhira Gandhi Memorial Hospital (IGMH) died
today [24 Jul 2011], taking this year's [2011] dengue death toll to
11. It is the highest number of dengue deaths recorded in a year in
the country http://www.haveeru.com.mv/english/details/37409. [A
HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of the Maldives can be accessed at
http://healthmap.org/r/0IpH. - Mod.TY]

Oceania - Australia. 24 Jul 2011. The Australian Red Cross had to
throw out 33 600 litres of donated blood for fear it was contaminated
with dengue fever [virus], after the large northern Queensland
outbreak in late 2009-10.

Disposing of 7 per cent of its blood supply cost the blood service
almost AUD 4 million [USD 4.28 million]. Australian Red Cross
executive director of research Dr David Irving said the recent problem
was brought home with the outbreak in northern Queensland, when more
than 1000 people were infected with dengue [viruses]
http://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/more-news/dengue-fever-threat-to-blood-supply/story-fn7x8me2-1226100473601.
[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Queensland can be accessed
at http://healthmap.org/r/008N. - Mod.TY]

Latin America - Brazil (Rio Claro, Sao Paulo state). 24 Jul 2011.
According to the bulletin of Epidemiological Surveillance issued on
Friday of last week [15 Jul 2011], there was a total of 1641 dengue
cases in the municipality since the beginning of this year [January
2011]. This is equivalent to the total tallied during all of 2007 [and
more than] 631 cases in the municipality in 2010
http://jornalcidade.uol.com.br/rioclaro/dia-a-dia/saude/79298--DENGUE:-numero-de-casos-ultrapassa-os-de-2007-e-Rio-Claro-ja-vive-sua-pior-epidemia--.
[in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY. A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map
of Rio Claro in Sao Paulo state can be accessed at
http://healthmap.org/r/0C7v. - Mod.TY]

Brazil (Mato Grosso state). 21 Jul 2011. The state Secretariat of
Health confirmed this Thursday [21 Jul 2011] the 6th dengue death. The
total reported cases of the disease in Mato Grosso from 1 Jan - 21 Jul
[2011] is 40 391, a decline of more than 32 000 in the reported cases
compared to the same period last year [2010]
http://g1.globo.com/mato-grosso/noticia/2011/07/estado-confirma-mais-uma-morte-por-dengue-em-mato-grosso.html.
[in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY; A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map
of Mato Grosso state can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/00L-.
- Mod.TY]
